entries.title: Job growth expected to have cooled in December but not enough to slow Fed rate hikes
entries.description: The economy is expected to have added 200,000 jobs in December, less than November, but still strong enough to keep the Fed aggressively fighting inflation.

entries.title: Ram previews new electric pickup to rival Ford, Rivian and others
entries.description: The Stellantis truck brand revealed the Ram 1500 Revolution BEV concept ahead of a production model that's expected to be unveiled in the coming months.

entries.title: I'm a psychology expert in Finland, the No. 1 happiest country in the world—here are 3 things we never do
entries.description: For five years in a row, Finland has been ranked the No. 1 happiest country in the world. A Finnish philosopher and psychology expert shares the habits that make people in Finland so exceptionally satisfied with their lives.

entries.title: California forces companies to show pay on job listings, revealing big tech salaries
entries.description: A new law that went into effect this week requires most California employers to disclose salaries on job listings.

entries.title: Delta plans to offer free Wi-Fi starting Feb. 1
entries.description: Delta's plan to make Wi-Fi free comes as airlines compete for customers in the travel rebound following the pandemic slump nearly three years ago.

entries.title: Crypto lender Genesis Trading lays off 30% of workforce
entries.description: Barry Silbert's Genesis Trading reduced headcount by 30%, or 60 jobs, as the crypto lender fends off a potential bankruptcy filing after the collapse of FTX.

entries.title: Here's how the House speaker debacle is paralyzing the U.S. Congress
entries.description: The failure to elect a House speaker has left the legislative branch of the government effectively paralyzed.

entries.title: China's new Covid surge is crippling the world's most important factories and biggest ports
entries.description: The surge in Covid-19 cases in China is impacting the completion of manufacturing orders, according to CNBC Supply Chain Heat Map data.

entries.title: These states will dominate EV battery manufacturing in 2030
entries.description: Georgia, Kentucky, and Michigan each have plans to stand up between 97 and 136 gigawatt hours of EV battery manufacturing capacity per year by 2030.

entries.title: Silvergate Capital tanks nearly 40% after crypto bank discloses massive fourth-quarter withdrawals
entries.description: The bank, which was tied to failed crypto exchange FTX, reported a decline of nearly 70% in customer deposits last quarter.

entries.title: Private payroll growth surged by 235,000 in December, well above estimate, ADP reports
entries.description: Private payrolls rose by 235,000 for the month, well ahead of the 153,000 Dow Jones estimate.

entries.title: Prince Harry reportedly alleges in new book that brother William physically attacked him
entries.description: Prince Harry's upcoming autobiography details an alleged fight in which his older brother, the future British king Prince William, pushed him to the floor, according to a report in The Guardian newspaper.

entries.title: Apple supplier Luxshare rises after reportedly winning contract to produce luxury iPhones
entries.description: Luxshare stocks rose after a report said the supplier is set to sign a contract to produce premium iPhones.

entries.title: EU recommends travelers from China to take a Covid test before entering Europe
entries.description: European nations agreed to recommend imposing new restrictions on travelers from China amid fears of an increase in Covid cases.

entries.title: Hong Kong stocks are off to their best start since 2018 on China recovery hopes
entries.description: Property and technology stocks continued to lift the Hang Seng index, which rose more than 3% in Wednesday's session.

entries.title: Amazon CEO Andy Jassy confirms company will cut over 18,000 jobs, more than initially planned
entries.description: Amazon has decided to get rid of additional roles after committing to a round of cuts in its corporate workforce in November.

entries.title: Samsung expected to post lowest quarterly profit in years due to memory chip 'market carnage'
entries.description: Samsung's profit could nosedive in the fourth quarter as memory prices have plunged sharply amid a lack of demand.
